Ode ΧΙΙ.

To Maecenas, for whom see 1. 1 and Introd. p. xiii.

Scheme. You would not like the stirring history of our race or the feats of heroes to be told in lyric verse, Maecenas. The exploits of Caesar, too, you can tell yourself better in prose. No: my theme shall be the beauty and constancy and grace of Licymnia, whom you would not exchange for all the wealth of Orient. Cf. 1. 6.
